latestPosts.caption:
Here’s my secret to staying lean throughout the year. Save and share it with a friend who needs to see this. 🫡 🥂 

❌ Processed Sugars : Cut down on sugary snacks, candies, and sugary beverages as excessive sugar intake can lead to fat gain and energy crashes. 

❌Processed Foods: Minimize processed foods that are high in additives, preservatives, and unhealthy fats.

❌Sodas and Sweetened beverages: These provide empty calories and can contribute to fat gain. Opt for water, herbal tea, or natural fruit juices in moderation. 

❌Highly Processed Carbohydrates: Limit refined carbs like white bread, sugary cereals, and pastries. Opt for complex carbs from whole grains and vegetables.

❌Trans Fats: Avoid or limit foods high in trans fats, often found in fried and processed foods, as they can negatively impact heart health.

❌Fried Foods: High in unhealthy fats, fried foods can contribute to inflammation and may hinder muscle recovery. 

❌Excessive Alcohol: While moderate alcohol consumption may be acceptable, excessive drinking can hinder muscle recovery and overall athletic performance.

And yes of course with this you need to workout regularly as well. You can’t skip that 😃🤙🏽

Unplugged 💆‍♂️🕊️☮️⛰️
